---
/**
 * Privacy Policy
 *
 * Covers the SignScan iOS app and the ssmit.com website.
 * Written to reflect how the product actually works: on-device processing,
 * no accounts, no analytics, purchases through Apple.
 */

import SubpageLayout from '@layouts/SubpageLayout.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '@lib/config';

const email = siteConfig.email;
---

<SubpageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How SignScan and ssmit.com handle your data: documents stay on your device, we run no accounts, no analytics, and no tracking."
  badge="Legal"
  subtitle="Effective July 19, 2026 · Applies to the SignScan app and ssmit.com"
  illustration="/illustrations/privacy-hero.svg"
  illustrationAlt=""
>
  <div class="callout">
    <p>
      <strong>The short version:</strong> SignScan is built so that we
      <em>cannot</em> see your documents. Everything — scanning, text
      recognition, signing, translation, redaction — runs on your iPhone.
      There are no accounts, no analytics, and no ads. The only personal data
      we ever receive is what you choose to send us yourself, like a support
      email.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    SSMIT ("we", "us") is a software studio based in Sacramento, California,
    and the maker of <strong>SignScan</strong>, a document scanning and
    signing app for iPhone. This policy covers the SignScan app and this
    website, ssmit.com. Questions about anything here are welcome at
    <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your documents stay on your device</h2>
  <p>
    Every document you scan, import, sign, or edit in SignScan is stored
    locally on your iPhone, inside the app's private container. All
    processing happens on-device:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Scanning and capture</strong> use the camera on your device only.</li>
    <li><strong>Text recognition (OCR) and handwriting reading</strong> use Apple's on-device Vision framework.</li>
    <li><strong>Translation</strong> uses Apple's on-device translation engine and works fully offline.</li>
    <li><strong>Redaction and blur</strong> permanently alter the document on your device.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We operate no servers that receive, store, or process your documents.
    Your documents leave your phone only when <em>you</em> export or share
    them — and then they go where you send them, not to us.
  </p>
  <p>
    Because documents live in the app's local storage, they are included in
    your device backups if you have iCloud Backup or local backups enabled.
    Those backups are governed by
    <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Apple's privacy policy</a>
    and your own iOS settings, not by us.
  </p>

  <h2>No accounts, no analytics, no tracking</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>SignScan has <strong>no sign-up and no user accounts</strong>.</li>
    <li>The app contains <strong>no analytics SDKs, no advertising SDKs, and no third-party trackers</strong>.</li>
    <li>We do not collect usage data, device identifiers, or location data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Device permissions the app asks for</h2>
  <p>SignScan requests system permissions only when a feature needs them:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Camera</strong> — to scan documents, IDs, and business cards. Images go straight into your local library.</li>
    <li><strong>Photo library</strong> — only if you import photos into a document.</li>
    <li><strong>Contacts</strong> — only if you use Business Card capture to save a scanned card. The card is saved through the system contacts sheet, under your control; we never read your existing contacts.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>You can revoke any permission at any time in iOS Settings.</p>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>
    SignScan Pro is sold through Apple's App Store (as a one-time purchase or
    a monthly subscription). Payment is processed entirely by Apple — we
    never see your name, card details, or billing address. The app validates
    your purchase on-device using Apple's StoreKit framework.
  </p>

  <h2>Data you choose to send us</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Support email.</strong> If you write to
      <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>, we receive your email address
      and whatever you include in the message. We use it only to help you,
      and we don't add you to any list.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Website forms.</strong> If you join a waitlist or notification
      list on ssmit.com, we store the email address you submit and use it
      only for the update you asked for. Unsubscribe by replying or using the
      link in any email.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we never do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We never sell or rent personal information.</li>
    <li>We never share your data with third parties for their marketing.</li>
    <li>We never use the contents of your documents for anything — we can't; we don't have them.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data retention and deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Your documents exist only on your device: deleting a document in the app
    removes it, and deleting the app removes everything the app stored. For
    anything you've sent us by email, write to
    <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a> and we'll delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    SignScan and ssmit.com are not directed at children under 13, and we do
    not knowingly collect personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we change this policy, we'll update this page and its effective date.
    A material change (there are no plans for one) would be called out in the
    app's release notes.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    SSMIT · Sacramento, California, USA<br />
    <a href={`mailto:${email}`}>{email}</a>
  </p>
</SubpageLayout>
